item.title: Microsoft Fabric Expert for Predictive Modeling Project (AutoML focus) - Upwork
item.description:
We are seeking a Microsoft Fabric expert to develop and implement a predictive modeling solution, with a primary focus on using Fabric's AutoML capabilities. We're also open to alternative approaches within the Fabric ecosystem if recommended. The ideal candidate will have extensive experience with Fabric's tools, especially its AutoML features.

Key Responsibilities:
1. Implement a predictive modeling solution primarily using Microsoft Fabric's AutoML capabilities
2. Set up data integration pipelines using Fabric's Data Factory
3. Utilize Fabric's lakehouse architecture for efficient data storage and management
4. Configure and run AutoML experiments in Synapse Analytics
5. Create interactive dashboards and reports with Power BI to visualize model outputs
6. Establish automated workflows for model retraining and scoring

Requirements:
- Proven expertise with Microsoft Fabric and its component services
- Strong understanding of and experience with Fabric's AutoML capabilities
- Experience with data integration and pipeline creation in Fabric
- Proficiency in using Synapse Analytics, particularly for AutoML experiments
- Skill in creating Power BI dashboards and reports
- Familiarity with MLflow for model management
- Understanding of data protection and governance within Fabric

Deliverables:
1. A fully implemented predictive modeling solution in Microsoft Fabric, preferably using AutoML
2. Data integration pipelines for continuous data ingestion
3. An interactive Power BI dashboard for visualizing model outputs
4. Automated workflows for model maintenance and scoring
5. Comprehensive documentation of the implemented solution, including AutoML experiment results

item.title: Power Business Intelligence Analyst  - Upwork
item.description:
Power Business Intelligence Analyst

Salary: Negotiable subject to skills and experience.

Requirements:
  
Male or Female
At least 5 years to 10 years’ experience
Certified Data Analytic
Business Analysis & Process Management
Portfolio of pervious project is needed.


Position Overview:
As a Power BI Developer at Scott Park Group Inc, you will play a crucial role in developing operational reports, automated dashboards, and insightful data presentations using Power BI and other reporting tools. You will collaborate closely with various stakeholders to understand business requirements and translate them into functional specifications for reporting applications. Additionally, you will leverage your expertise in database fundamentals to ensure efficient data extraction, shaping, and validation for reporting and analytics solutions.

Key Accountabilities:
Develop operational reports such as dealing and financial system extracts:
• Design and implement operational reports to extract relevant data from various systems and databases.
• Ensure accuracy and efficiency in data extraction processes to meet business needs.
Develop automated reports and dashboards using Power BI and other reporting tools:
• Utilize Power BI and other reporting tools to automate report generation processes.
• Design and create interactive dashboards to visualize data insights effectively.
Understand business requirements to set functional specifications for reporting applications:
• Collaborate with stakeholders to comprehend business objectives and requirements.
• Translate business needs into detailed functional specifications for reporting applications.
Have a great skill in extracting report presentation for the management:
• Develop visually appealing and insightful report presentations tailored for management review.
• Ensure clarity and relevance of information presented to facilitate decision-making processes.
Implement Application Lifecycle Management (ALM) practices:
• Establish and maintain effective ALM practices to manage the lifecycle of reporting applications.
• Coordinate with development teams to ensure seamless integration and deployment of reporting solutions.
Documentation:
• Create comprehensive documentation for reporting applications, including design specifications, user guides, and technical documentation.
• Maintain accurate and up-to-date documentation to support ongoing development and maintenance efforts.
Facilitate Testing:
• Develop and execute testing strategies to ensure the quality and reliability of reporting applications.
• Collaborate with QA teams to conduct thorough testing, identify defects, and implement necessary fixes.
Version Control:
• Implement version control systems to manage code and configuration changes for reporting applications.
• Ensure proper versioning and tracking of changes to maintain a reliable development environment.

Tools:
• MS SQL Server BI Stack (including SSRS and TSQL)
• Power BI
• Power Query
• MDX
• DAX

Skills, Knowledge, and Experience:
• Ability to quickly stage and shape data from various sources into reporting and analytics                
               solutions.
• Experience in creating functional financial reporting.
• Deep understanding of database fundamentals, including relational and multidimensional
              database design.
• Proficiency in the use of query and reporting analysis tools.
• Strong skills in standardizing data collection through database design and validation reports.
• Experience in providing application analysis and data modeling design for centralized data    
              warehousing.
Additional Qualifications:
• Experience with data visualization best practices.
• Strong analytical and problem-solving skills.
• Excellent communication and collaboration abilities.



Portfolio of Previous Projects Required:

Candidates must provide a portfolio showcasing previous Power BI development projects. This portfolio should highlight the candidate's ability to design and implement operational reports, automated dashboards, and data presentations using Power BI and other relevant tools. The portfolio should demonstrate the candidate's proficiency in data visualization, report customization, and data extraction techniques.

Note: Exclusively for Filipino Applicants

Question:
Description

The objective is to improve the agents’ existing knowledge used for agent segmentation in a supervised predictive framework.

Problem Statement Scenario:

An insurance group consists of 10 property and casualty insurance, life insurance and insurance brokerage companies. The property and casualty companies in the group operate in a 17-state region. The group consists of major regional property and casualty insurer, represented by more than 4,000 independent agents who live and work in local communities through a six-state region. Define the metrics to analyze agent performance based on several attributes like demography, products sold, new business, etc.

Below are the Visualization charts that need to be incorporated:

a. Summary stats by agency

b. Product line: Commercial Line/Personal Line wise analysis

c. Agency wise and state-wise distribution of Retention Ratio (Top 10)

d. Hit ratio distribution across different Quotes-systems (also by PL/CL)

e. Add a few more based on your understanding of the data

Growth rates from 2006 to 2013 have to be computed and converted to independent attributes and included in the data for modeling.
Compute Hit ratio based on bounds and quotes for each Quotes-system
Compute required aggregations at Agency ID, state, and year
Decide if binning the data works for this situation

item.title: Power BI Expert| SAP Data Modeling| Financial Analyst - Upwork
item.description:
Job Overview:
We are seeking a highly skilled and experienced Financial System Analyst to join our team. This role is flexible, offering both part-time and full-time opportunities depending on your availability and skillset. You will be required to log in remotely and work on tasks that may be time-tracked

Key Responsibilities:

Data Analysis & Reporting:

Create insightful and visually appealing reports from SQL databases (SAP, SQL Server, Oracle, Snowflake) and Excel files using Power BI.

Utilize Python for data manipulation, analysis, and machine learning tasks to derive actionable insights.
Set up and manage KPI tracking systems within Power BI.

Problem-Solving & Innovation:

Ask the right questions to understand business needs and translate them into effective business intelligence reports.
Proactively identify and solve data issues, such as missing or inconsistent data, and ensure data quality.
Innovate new analytical solutions to meet unmet customer needs, using current and emerging statistical, machine learning, and data science methods.

Collaboration & Communication:

Work closely with senior executives to condense disparate data into succinct, actionable insights.
Clearly and succinctly communicate analytical results and recommendations to stakeholders.
Collaborate creatively with team members and stakeholders to deliver high-value analytical services.

Documentation:

Translate business requirements into technical specifications.
Document processes, methodologies, and results to ensure transparency and reproducibility.

Required Qualifications:

High-speed internet connection and a computer with at least 16GB of RAM.
Extensive experience with Microsoft Power BI, including DAX and M code.
Strong proficiency in SQL and familiarity with databases like SAP, or Snowflake.
A demonstrated ability to validate and ensure the accuracy of your work.

Preferred Qualifications:

Experience with Python, particularly in the context of data analysis and machine learning.
Experience with SAP systems and financial data analysis.


Key Attributes:

A proactive problem solver who doesn’t just follow orders but brings innovative solutions to the table.
An inquisitive mind that digs deep into the data to extract meaningful insights.
Ability to work independently and take ownership of projects from start to finish.
Excellent communication skills, both written and verbal, with the ability to explain complex concepts to non-technical stakeholders.


Hourly Range: $10.00-$30.00
Posted On: August 17, 2024 14:58 UTC
Category: Data Analytics
Skills:SQL, Microsoft Power BI, Data Analysis, Data Visualization, Machine Learning, Deep Learning, Salesforce, Finance, R
Skills: SQL, Microsoft Power BI, Data Analysis, Data Visualization, Machine Learning, Deep Learning, Salesforce, Finance, R
Country: United States
